📊 Aggregate Planning & Quality Control Analysis
This project demonstrates the implementation of **Aggregate Planning** and **Quality Control** using **Microsoft Excel**. The analysis focuses on comparing production planning strategies and evaluating process stability through Statistical Process Control (SPC).

Project Objectives
- Compare different aggregate planning strategies.
- Analyze production costs under each strategy.
- Evaluate process stability using a c-Chart.
- Support production planning and quality improvement through data analysis.

Analysis Included
Aggregate Planning
The project compares three production planning strategies:
- Level Strategy
- Chase Strategy
- Subcontract Strategy

Each strategy is evaluated based on:
- Labor Cost
- Inventory Holding Cost
- Hiring Cost
- Layoff Cost
- Subcontracting Cost
- Total Production Cost

Statistical Quality Control (SPC)
A "c-Chart" is constructed to monitor the number of nonconformities during the production process.

The analysis includes:
- Center Line (C̄)
- Upper Control Limit (UCL)
- Lower Control Limit (LCL)
- Process Stability Evaluation

Tools
- Microsoft Excel
- Aggregate Planning
- Statistical Process Control (SPC)
- c-Chart
